info.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued February 21 at 3:30AM PST until February 21 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Minor coastal flooding expected. * WHERE...Portions of northwest and west central Washington. * WHEN...From 4 AM to 10 AM PST Tuesday. * IMPACTS...Minor coastal flooding due to tidal overflow is expected around high tide. This may lead to flooding of parking lots, parks, and roads, with only isolated road closures expected. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Inundation of up to 0.5 feet above ground level is possible along shorelines and low-lying coastal areas.
info.instruction: If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property. Inundation above ground level refers to the height above the Mean Higher High Water (MHHW) level.
